00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:04.320
Welcome my friend to today's
lecture on Know Your Customer.

00:00:04.860 --> 00:00:09.480
Let's unpack the mystery of this
concept without needing a PhD or a

00:00:09.480 --> 00:00:12.210
panic attack concept explanation.

00:00:13.590 --> 00:00:17.550
So what is this KYC that
everyone keeps talking about?

00:00:18.120 --> 00:00:20.460
Imagine a bank asking a new customer.

00:00:20.670 --> 00:00:21.900
Hello, G. Who are you?

00:00:21.900 --> 00:00:24.600
Really that my friend is KYC.

00:00:24.600 --> 00:00:29.580
In a nutshell, it is a mandatory,
not optional process for banks and

00:00:29.610 --> 00:00:33.840
all financial institutions to verify
the identity of their customers.

00:00:34.419 --> 00:00:39.190
This isn't just about nosy, it
involves collecting and then double

00:00:39.190 --> 00:00:43.209
checking personal information and
documents to be absolutely sure

00:00:43.300 --> 00:00:45.370
that you are who you claim to be.

00:00:45.879 --> 00:00:51.459
The main mission, the ultimate goal of
KYC is to prevent all sorts of financial,

00:00:51.459 --> 00:00:55.385
hanky panky, like money laundering,
terrorist financing, and fraud.

00:00:55.835 --> 00:01:00.515
How By understanding a customer's
financial habits and figuring out

00:01:00.515 --> 00:01:04.865
the risks they might bring, it
helps banks create a sort of kundy

00:01:04.895 --> 00:01:06.545
or profile for their customers.

00:01:06.965 --> 00:01:11.225
Keep an eye on their transactions, and
if something looks fishy, report it

00:01:11.225 --> 00:01:13.235
to the big bosses, the authorities.

00:01:14.565 --> 00:01:15.885
Real world relevance.

00:01:16.425 --> 00:01:21.945
Now, why is this so critical for a big
shot like a CBO or Chief Business Officer?

00:01:22.455 --> 00:01:24.255
It's about protecting the bank.

00:01:24.405 --> 00:01:27.735
It's their shield for
financial crime prevention.

00:01:27.914 --> 00:01:32.350
KYC is the chalky D, the very
first line of defense against money

00:01:32.550 --> 00:01:34.190
laundering and terrorist financing.

00:01:34.975 --> 00:01:40.015
It's also about regulatory compliance,
making sure the bank follows all the rules

00:01:40.075 --> 00:01:45.265
laid down by the RBI and other regulatory
bodies, so nobody gets a scolding.

00:01:45.925 --> 00:01:49.315
It is a key part of risk
management, helping to assess

00:01:49.315 --> 00:01:52.530
and manage the dangers that come
with different customer profiles.

00:01:53.360 --> 00:01:56.780
For customer onboarding, it's
the fundamental first step

00:01:56.780 --> 00:01:59.840
to build a legitimate and
secure banking relationship.

00:02:00.320 --> 00:02:02.570
Let's not forget reputation protection.

00:02:02.870 --> 00:02:06.320
It guards the bank's good name
and the trust people have in it.

00:02:06.650 --> 00:02:11.570
And finally, it promotes ethical banking,
pushing for transparency and honest

00:02:11.570 --> 00:02:13.820
practices in the whole financial world.

