00:03:04.665 --> 00:03:05.985
Formulas and tricks.

00:03:06.345 --> 00:03:07.365
Now relax.

00:03:07.575 --> 00:03:10.815
KYC doesn't have any scary
mathematical formulas.

00:03:11.085 --> 00:03:15.015
Instead, it's all about remembering
some key names and ideas.

00:03:15.285 --> 00:03:17.205
Think of these as your cheat codes.

00:03:17.535 --> 00:03:19.155
First, always remember.

00:03:19.210 --> 00:03:20.740
PMLA 2002.

00:03:21.040 --> 00:03:25.270
That's the prevention of Money
Laundering Act 2002, the big boss,

00:03:25.330 --> 00:03:27.640
the primary law for KYC in India.

00:03:28.090 --> 00:03:30.460
The RBI guidelines are also crucial.

00:03:30.730 --> 00:03:34.870
The Reserve Bank of India gives
out the detailed rule book for KYC

00:03:34.870 --> 00:03:36.935
and anti-money laundering or a ML.

00:03:37.525 --> 00:03:42.234
On the world stage, we have FATF,
the Financial Action Task Force,

00:03:42.325 --> 00:03:45.385
which sets the international
standards that India follows.

00:03:45.805 --> 00:03:46.915
Within the process.

00:03:46.975 --> 00:03:50.695
You have C, D, D, or customer
due diligence, which is just

00:03:50.695 --> 00:03:53.519
the fancy term for identifying
and verifying the customer.

00:03:54.310 --> 00:03:56.440
For very important or risky people.

00:03:56.589 --> 00:04:00.880
There's ED, D or enhanced due
diligence for low risk customers.

00:04:00.970 --> 00:04:03.670
We have SDD Simplified Due Diligence.

00:04:04.060 --> 00:04:08.589
The documents needed are simple,
POI, or proof of identity, like

00:04:08.589 --> 00:04:13.595
a pan card or passport and POA or
proof of address like a utility bill.

00:04:14.019 --> 00:04:17.380
And finally, remember that
customers are sorted into risk

00:04:17.380 --> 00:04:19.810
categories, low, medium, or high.

00:04:21.015 --> 00:04:22.245
Methods of solving.

00:04:22.664 --> 00:04:27.914
When we say methods of solving for KYC,
we mean the steps a bank actually takes.

00:04:28.245 --> 00:04:31.364
First is the customer
acceptance policy or cap.

00:04:31.695 --> 00:04:35.325
The bank must have clear rules
for who it accepts as a customer.

00:04:35.474 --> 00:04:37.815
No ghost accounts and fake names allowed.

00:04:38.205 --> 00:04:41.445
This also includes rules for when
they might have to say, Tata,

00:04:41.445 --> 00:04:42.974
bye-bye, and close an account.

00:04:43.515 --> 00:04:47.234
Next is the customer
identification procedure or CIP.

00:04:47.625 --> 00:04:49.005
This is the paperwork part.

00:04:49.244 --> 00:04:53.804
Collecting documents for POI and POA,
and then checking if they are real.

00:04:54.255 --> 00:04:57.015
Then comes the risk
management framework here.

00:04:57.104 --> 00:05:01.844
The bank plays detective, categorizing
customers into low, medium, or high

00:05:01.844 --> 00:05:05.354
risk based on things like their
job income and where they live.

00:05:05.775 --> 00:05:09.015
Based on this risk, they apply
the right level of diligence

00:05:09.375 --> 00:05:10.875
after the account is open.

00:05:10.965 --> 00:05:13.725
The work continues with
monitoring of transactions.

00:05:13.995 --> 00:05:17.955
The bank continuously watches for
any weird or suspicious activity.

00:05:18.315 --> 00:05:20.475
And finally, there is record keeping.

00:05:20.745 --> 00:05:25.095
The bank must keep all KYC records
for at least five years after the

00:05:25.095 --> 00:05:28.455
customer relationship ends, just in
case someone needs to check them later.

